Tottenham Has 6-Month Profit of 4.2 Million Pounds After Year-Earlier Loss

-- B y   C h r i s   E l s e r
-- 
2011-03-31T14:15:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/tottenham-has-6-month-profit-of-4-2-million-pounds-after-year-earlier-loss.html
Tottenham Hotspur, which faces Real
 Madrid  in the Champions League quarterfinals next week, had a
half-year profit of 4.2 million pounds ($6.7 million) as it
benefited from playing in the European soccer competition.  The team had a loss of 6.1 million pounds in the year-
earlier period, according to a Regulatory News Service statement
today. Revenue rose 49 percent to 79.76 million pounds as the
team gained sales from Champions League games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Elser at 
 celser@bloomberg.net  